{"_id":"GlShFJF2TpsNh1FX","name":"Torn Arm Muscle (Minor)","permission":{"default":0,"oTi5e7Dr05zb56mO":3},"type":"injury","data":{"description":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":"<p>A muscle has been sprained or torn, impairing your capabilities. &nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Arm:&nbsp;</strong>Suffer a penalty of -10 to all Tests involving the arm</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Healing: </span>The muscle will partially heal in 30 - Toughness Bonus days. Use of the Healing Skill will reduce the time by 1 day, plus a further day per SL (can only gain this once)&nbsp;</p>"},"gmdescription":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":""},"location":{"value":"Arm","type":"String","label":"Location"},"penalty":{"value":"-10 to Tests involving (specific) Arm","type":"String","label":"Penalty"},"duration":{"label":"Duration","value":"30 - TB","type":"String","active":false,"permanent":false},"source":{"type":"String","label":"Source"}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/wfrp4e-core/icons/injuries/tornarm.png","effects":[{"_id":"9rO0RdQJqsNwv9lv","flags":{"wfrp4e":{"effectTrigger":"dialogChoice","effectApplication":"actor","effectData":{"description":"Using arm with Torn Muscle","modifier":-10,"slBonus":null,"successBonus":null,"difficultyStep":null},"preventDuplicateEffects":false}},"changes":[],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"modules/wfrp4e-core/icons/injuries/tornarm.png","label":"Torn Arm Muscle","tint":"","transfer":true}]}
{"_id":"MnMZv7ZXoRqoH9dS","name":"Amputated Arm","permission":{"default":0,"oTi5e7Dr05zb56mO":3},"type":"injury","data":{"description":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":"<p>Whenever you suffer a Critical Wound marked Amputation (Difficulty) you must pass an Endurance test of the corresponding difficulty or gain a @Condition[Prone] Condition. On a Failure (-2) or worse, you gain a @Condition[Stunned] Condition; on an impressive Failure (-4 or worse), gain an @Condition[Unconscious] condition</p>\n<p>All amputations require Surgery to heal properly, meaning 1 Wound cannot be healed until you visit a surgeon. See @JournalEntry[Healing]{Surgey}</p>\n<p><strong>Arm</strong>: You take a &ndash;20 penalty on all Tests that rely on the use of two hands and you cannot wield two-handed weapons. Should the lost hand be your primary hand, you take the customary &ndash;20 penalty to Melee Tests made with weapons using your secondary hand. For every 100 XP you spend, you can reduce this penalty by 5 as you relearn how to do everything with the other hand. If you lose both hands, it is probably time to master hook fighting</p>"},"gmdescription":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":""},"location":{"value":"Arm","type":"String","label":"Location"},"penalty":{"value":"-20 when relying on two hands","type":"String","label":"Penalty"},"duration":{"label":"Duration","value":"","type":"String","active":false,"permanent":true},"source":{"type":"String","label":"Source"}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/wfrp4e-core/icons/injuries/amputatedarm.png","effects":[{"_id":"qPV4jIDGN9onOAYV","flags":{"wfrp4e":{"effectTrigger":"dialogChoice","effectApplication":"actor","effectData":{"description":"Relies on two hands","modifier":-20,"slBonus":null,"successBonus":null,"difficultyStep":null},"preventDuplicateEffects":false}},"changes":[],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"modules/wfrp4e-c