{"_id":"nbhn2wX35b7Jrcbg","name":"Broken Head (Minor)","permission":{"default":0,"oTi5e7Dr05zb56mO":3},"type":"injury","data":{"description":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":"<p>A bone has been fractured, but still aligned.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Head:</span><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">&nbsp;</span>Down to a liquid diet and will suffer a penalty of -30 to all Language Tests.&nbsp;</p>\n<h3>Healing</h3>\n<p>A fracture takes 30+1d10 days to heal. At the end, a successful Average (+20) Endurance test means the bone healed well. Otherwise: Penalty of -5 to spoken Language Tests</p>\n<p>A successful <strong>Average (+20)</strong> Heal Test within a week of receiving the fracture will negate the need for Endurance Test. But the area must remain bound and held in place for the duration of healing. If binding is undone, another Average (+20) Heal Test enacted within a day will need to be passed to avoid the Endurance Test.</p>"},"gmdescription":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":""},"location":{"value":"Head","type":"String","label":"Location"},"penalty":{"value":"-30 to all Language Tests.","type":"String","label":"Penalty"},"duration":{"label":"Duration","value":"","type":"String","active":false,"permanent":false},"source":{"type":"String","label":"Source"}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/wfrp4e-core/icons/injuries/head.png","effects":[{"_id":"WtbK1vMvsJYKBbWj","flags":{"wfrp4e":{"effectApplication":"actor","preventDuplicateEffects":false,"effectTrigger":"prefillDialog","script":"if (args.type == \"cast\" || (args.type == \"skill\" && args.item.name.includes(game.i18n.localize(\"Language\"))))\n   args.prefillModifiers.modifier -= 30"}},"changes":[],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"modules/wfrp4e-core/icons/injuries/head.png","label":"Broken Head","tint":"","transfer":true}]}
{"_id":"qn4ZpvTQIX4rcJDl","name":"Torn Arm Muscle (Major)","permission":{"default":0,"oTi5e7Dr05zb56mO":3},"type":"injury","data":{"description":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":"<p>A muscle has been sprained or torn, impairing your capabilities. &nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Arm:&nbsp;</strong>Suffer a penalty of -20 to all Tests involving the arm</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Healing: </span>The muscle will partially heal in 30 &ndash; your Toughness Bonus days, after which the penalty for using the limb reduces to &ndash;10 to all relevant Tests. The muscle will completely heal after another 30 &ndash; your Toughness Bonus days. Use of the Healing skill does little but inform you not to use the affected Hit Location.</p>"},"gmdescription":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":""},"location":{"value":"Arm","type":"String","label":"Location"},"penalty":{"value":"-20 to Tests involving (specific) Arm","type":"String","label":"Penalty"},"duration":{"label":"Duration","value":"30 - TB","type":"String","active":false,"permanent":false},"source":{"type":"String","label":"Source"}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/wfrp4e-core/icons/injuries/tornarm.png","effects":[{"_id":"GUbysJIeA44LNOIq","flags":{"wfrp4e":{"effectTrigger":"dialogChoice","effectApplication":"actor","effectData":{"description":"","modifier":null,"slBonus":null,"successBonus":null,"difficultyStep":null},"preventDuplicateEffects":false}},"changes":[],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"modules/wfrp4e-core/icons/injuries/tornarm.png","label":"Torn Arm Muscle","tint":"","transfer":true}]}
{"_id":"rkJA1DlK51QuRlJy","name":"Amputated Tongue","permission":{"default":0,"oTi5e7Dr05zb56mO":3},"type":"injury","data":{"description":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":"<p>Whenever you suffer a Critical Wound marked Amputation (Difficulty) you must pass an Endurance test of the corresponding difficulty or gain a @Condition[Prone] Condition. On a Failure (-2) or worse, you gain a @Condition[Stunned] Condition; on an impressive Failure (-4 or worse), gain an @Condition[Unconscious] condition</p>\n<p>All amputations require Surgery to heal properly, meaning 1 Wound cannot be healed until you visit a surgeon. See @JournalEntry[Healing]{Surgey}</p>\n<p><strong>Tongue: </strong>A loss of a tongue leaves you grunting and humming, or relying on make-shift sign language, for communication. You automatically fail all Language Tests involving speaking.</p>"},"gmdescription":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":""},"location":{"value":"Tongue","type":"String","label":"Location"},"penalty":{"value":"Fail all Language Tests","type":"String","label":"Penalty"},"duration":{"label":"Duration","value":"","type":"String","active":false,"permanent":true},"source":{"type":"String","label":"Source"}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/wfrp4e-core/icons/injuries/injury.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"rlDZZTj5PXjuRXa2","name":"Broken Arm (Major)","permission":{"default":0,"oTi5e7Dr05zb56mO":3},"type":"injury","data":{"description":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":"<p>A bone is badly broken, either resting at an odd angle or has splintered at the point of breakage. The Hit Location is effectively unusable until healing.</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Arm:&nbsp;</span>You are down to one limb as the other is too painful to use, and may require binding. You take a &ndash;20 penalty on all Tests that rely on the use of two hands and you cannot wield two-handed weapons; Should the lost hand be your primary hand, you take the customary &ndash;20 penalty to Melee Tests made with weapons using your secondary hand.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3>Healing</h3>\n<p>A broken bone takes 40+1d10 days to heal. At the end, a successful <strong>Challenging (+0) Endurance</strong> test means the bone healed well. Otherwise: Penalty of -10 to all Agility Tests using the arm.</p>\n<p>A successful <strong>Average (+20)</strong> Heal Test within a week of receiving the fracture will negate the need for Endurance Test. But the area must remain bound and held in place for the duration of healing. If binding is undone, another <strong>Average (+20) Heal</strong> Test enacted within a day will need to be passed to avoid the Endurance Test.</p>"},"gmdescription":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":""},"location":{"value":"Arm","type":"String","label":"Location"},"penalty":{"value":"-20 when relying on two hands","type":"String","label":"Penalty"},"duration":{"label":"Duration","value":"40+1d10","type":"String","active":false,"permanent":false},"source":{"type":"String","label":"Source"}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/wfrp4e-core/icons/injuries/broken-arm.png","effects":[{"_id":"m1KbLc6l2LK76961","flags":{"wfrp4e":{"effectTrigger":"dialogChoice","effectApplication":"actor","effectData":{"description":"Test relies on both hands.","modifier":-20,"slBonus":null,"successBonus":null,"difficultyStep":null},"preventDuplicateEffects":false,"hide":false}},"changes":[],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"modules/wfrp4e-core/icons/injuries/broken-arm.png","label":"Broken Arm","tint":"","transfer":true}]}
{"_id":"weczkAMPlTjX7lqU","name":"Amputated Eye","permission":{"default":0,"oTi5e7Dr05zb56mO":3},"type":"injury","data":{"description":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":"<p>Whenever you suffer a Critical Wound marked Amputation (Difficulty) you must pass an Endurance test of the corresponding difficulty or gain a @Condition[Prone] Condition. On a Failure (-2) or worse, you gain a @Condition[Stunned] Condition; on an impressive Failure (-4 or worse), gain an @Condition[Unconscious] condition</p>\n<p>All amputations require Surgery to heal properly, meaning 1 Wound cannot be healed until you visit a surgeon. See @JournalEntry[Healing]{Surgey}</p>\n<p><strong>Eye</strong>: For all losing an eye is horrendous, but you soon learn to compensate. Should you have the misfortune to lose both eyes, suffer a penalty of &ndash;30 to all Tests inﬂuenced by sight, such as Weapon Tests, Dodge Tests, Ride Tests, and similar. Further, you suffer a penalty of &ndash;5 to all Fellowship Tests per scarred socket others can see</p>"},"gmdescription":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":""},"location":{"value":"Eye","type":"String","label":"Location"},"penalty":{"value":"-5 Fellowship","type":"String","label":"Penalty"},"duration":{"label":"Duration","value":"","type":"String","active":false,"permanent":true},"source":{"type":"String","label":"Source"}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/wfrp4e-core/icons/injuries/amputatedeye.png","effects":[{"_id":"HK53YUZJx5byXmup","flags":{"wfrp4e":{"effectTrigger":"dialogChoice","effectApplication":"actor","effectData":{"description":"Relies on sight","modifier":-30,"slBonus":null,"successBonus":null,"difficultyStep":null},"preventDuplicateEffects":false}},"changes":[],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"modules/wfrp4e-core/icons/injuries/amputatedeye.png","label":"Lost Both Eyes","tint":"","transfer":true},{"_id":"OBcPvTtXweBfzAaU","flags":{"wfrp4e":{"effectApplication":"actor","preventDuplicateEffects":false,"effectTrigger":"prefillDialog","script":"if (args.type == \"characteristic\" && args.item == \"fel\")\n      args.prefillModifiers.modifier -= 5\n\n    else if (args.type == \"skill\") {\n      if (args.item.data.characteristic.value == \"fel\")\n        args.prefillModifiers.modifier -= 5\n    }"}},"changes":[{"key":"","value":"","mode":2}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"modules/wfrp4e-core/icons/injuries/amputatedeye.png","label":"Lost Eye","tint":"","transfer":true}]}
{"_id":"zyocWSzEZEC826NS","name":"Amputated Hand","permission":{"default":0,"oTi5e7Dr05zb56mO":3},"type":"injury","data":{"description":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":"<p>Whenever you suffer a Critical Wound marked Amputation (Difficulty) you must pass an Endurance test of the corresponding difficulty or gain a @Condition[Prone] Condition. On a Failure (-2) or worse, you gain a @Condition[Stunned] Condition; on an impressive Failure (-4 or worse), gain an @Condition[Unconscious] condition</p>\n<p>All amputations require Surgery to heal properly, meaning 1 Wound cannot be healed until you visit a surgeon. See @JournalEntry[Healing]{Surgey}</p>\n<p><strong>Hand:&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp;You take a &ndash;20 penalty on all Tests that rely on the use of two hands and you cannot wield two-handed weapons; however, a shield can be strapped to the injured arm. Should the lost hand be your primary hand, you take the customary &ndash;20 penalty to Melee Tests made with weapons using your secondary hand. For every 100 XP you spend, you can reduce this penalty by 5 as you relearn how to do everything with the other hand. If you lose both hands, it is probably time to master hook fighting</p>"},"gmdescription":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":""},"location":{"value":"Hand","type":"String","label":"Location"},"penalty":{"value":"-20 when relying on two hands","type":"String","label":"Penalty"},"duration":{"label":"Duration","value":"","type":"String","active":false,"permanent":true},"source":{"type":"String","label":"Source"}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/wfrp4e-core/icons/injuries/amputatedhand.png","effects":[{"_id":"rTIWkLVhHcMduvPJ","flags":{"wfrp4e":{"effectTrigger":"dialogChoice","effectApplication":"actor","effectData":{"description":"Relies on two hands","modifier":-20,"slBonus":null,"successBonus":null,"difficultyStep":null},"preventDuplicateEffects":false}},"changes":[],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"modules/wfrp4e-core/icons/injuries/amputatedhand.png","label":"Amputated Hand","tint":"","transfer":true}]}
